    .block-xs-middle.pb-5
      .container
        .row
          .mx-auto.d-block.alexa
            = image_tag "echo_dot_home.png", width: 300
        .row
          .text-center style=("width: 100%")
            h1.block-titleData.frequency Meet your new receptionist
            p.lead.mb-4.text-muted Let your employees focus on more important tasks while Alexa receives your office visitors.
            a href="#pricing"
              button.btn.btn-outline-primary.btn-outline-home.btn-lg Get started
  #why.block.block-secondary
    .container
      .row.app-align-center
        .col-md-5.hidden-md-down
          = image_tag "alexa_dot_w.jpg"
        .col-lg-6.offset-md-1.col-md-12.offset-sm-0
          h6.text-muted.text-uppercase Why use Front Desk?
          h3 Less interruptions lead to better results and happier employees
          .row
            .col-sm-6.mb-3
              h5 Better results
              p
                | According to a study by Gloria Mark at UC Irvine, it takes a knowledge worker almost 
                | <b>25 minutes</b> to regain focus after having been interrupted. The work task in this study was 
                | writing emails. We believe that the costs can be even higher for tasks demanding high levels of focus 
                | , like programming.
                br
                br
                a.text-primary href="https://www.fastcompany.com/944128/worker-interrupted-cost-task-switching" target="_blank" Learn more
            .col-sm-6
              h5 Happiness
              p
                | The same study found that employees that are interrupted frequently are able to compensate for 
                | interruptions by working faster. But this comes at another cost: After only 20 minutes of 
                | interrupted performance people reported significantly higher stress, frustration, 
                | workload, effort, and pressure.
                br
                br
                a.text-primary href="https://www.ics.uci.edu/~gmark/chi08-mark.pdf" target="_blank" Learn more
  .block.block-inverse.block-secondary.app-code-block
    .container
      .row.app-align-center
        .col-md-5.push-md-7
          pre.app-code
            | Monthly distractions:          100 (~5 per day)
            br
            | Cost per distraction:          25 minutes
            br
            | Total time distracted:         41.67 hours
            br
            | Hourly employee cost:          31.25 $ (60k/yr)
            br
            |-----------------------------------------------
            br
            | Total cost per month:          1,302.18 $
        .col-md-6.pull-md-5
          h6.text-muted.text-uppercase Cost savings
          h3 Unlock thousands of dollars in lost productivity
          p.lead.mb-4.text-muted
            | To give you a feeling for how much you can gain from using Front Desk, we made a simple back-of-the-envelope 
            | calculation: If your employees were making about 60,000 $ per year on average and you have about 5 office visiors 
            | coming in every day, you are losing over 1,300 $ every month from employees handling visitors.
  .block.block-inverse.app-high-praise style=("background-image: url(#{image_path "startup-3.jpg"});")
    .container
      .row.app-align-center.py-3
        .col-sm-5.push-sm-7.py-5
